The evidence with the title 'How to reduce shootings - the New York Times ' says Nov 6, 2017  ... The first step is to understand the scale of the challenge America faces : the U.S. has more than 300 million guns – roughly one for every citizen – and stands out as well for its gun death rates . At the other extreme, Japan has less than one gun per 100 people , and typically fewer than 10 gun deaths a year  ... 
